Section Chief: ...Are you alright?
Yeah, somehow...
But...
Section Chief: What the... for such a pebble...
Prison Officer: Hey, what's the commotion!
Prison Officer: What the hell is this about!!
Prison Officer: Say something!!

Section Chief: I apologize... It was my lack of supervision
that caused the collapse during work...

Section Chief: One of the miners was buried under the rubble
during the excavation, and probably...

Prison Officer: That's not it!! What happened to the mined
ore and crystals...!!
Section Chief: ──...

Section Chief: It was so sudden that we couldn't take them
out, they must be buried under the rubble as well...
Prison Officer: Aaah!? Hey you bastard!!

Prison Officer: What do you think you're here for!? To dig
up stones, right!? And what's this!? You saved yourself but
didn't protect the stones!?

Prison Officer: You're supposed to protect the stones even
if it kills you!? That's your only value! There are plenty
of others to replace you!!
Section Chief: Aguu...! Ugh...!!
Prison Officer: Tch! Useless trash...!!

Prison Officer: Hey you scum!! You're also responsible for
just watching and not moving the mined stones!!

Prison Officer: There are so many of you, yet all you did
was stand there with your thumbs in your mouths! Is there no
one who can do their job properly!!

Prison Officer: All of you! Every single one of you will be
given the appropriate punishment!! Look forward to it!!

You bastards!! What do you think a worker's life is
worth...!!
Section Chief: Cough... Please, wait...
Section Chief: I truly... am sorry.

Section Chief: But this is... the responsibility of me, the
supervisor... my sole responsibility...

Section Chief: I will accept any punishment, so please...
spare the others... they are innocent...
Hey... you...!!

Section Chief: It's alright... The others have nothing to do
with this. I'm the cause. Getting heated and arguing was my
downfall. I'm the only one at fault here.
Section Chief: Truly, please, I beg of you...
Prison Officer: ──... Is that so. How noble of you.
Prison Officer: That's right. You guys are lucky.

Prison Officer: The kind and gentle Section Chief is going
to suffer for all of you!
Prison Officer: Fufufufufu...!!

Prison Officer: I just happened to break the toy I was using
before. This is perfect.
Section Chief: ...
Hey...! Do you realize what you're saying!?
Section Chief: ...
Hey!!! Say something...!!
Prison Officer: Shut up already!!
Prison Officer: You sewer rat! Just lie there and sleep!!
Prison Officer: Hey! Take her away before I change my mind!!

Prison Officer: Hey, you scum!! Don't just stand there!! Get
back to work immediately!!

Prison Officer: Don't even think about getting food until
you make up for the time you've wasted! Got it?!?
Wait, please!
Prison Officer: Huh?

She said what she said earlier, but as someone in the same
work group, I also share some responsibility for the
accident!

I can't let her take all the blame! I have an obligation to
be punished as well! I will accept punishment! So,
please...!
Prison Officer: Hah?

I understand she has her own resolve. But I cannot stand by
while someone else is sacrificed so that I can be protected.

I'm aware that I'm asking for too much!! But I will accept
punishment! So, is there any way you could lighten her
sentence, even just a little?

Prison Officer: You're getting shielded and you should just
keep quiet. Are you stupid?

Prison Officer: Besides, do you think you're in any position
to give me orders? Save your sleep talk for when you're
asleep, rat.
If I've offended you, I apologize. However... but still!

Please! Truly, even though it was for a short time, she took
care of me! If she hadn't treated my wounds, by now I
wouldn't be here... no, I might not even be alive...

As a knight, no, as a person, I owe her a debt of gratitude
that must be repaid!

I'll do anything! I'll take the punishment in her place! I
don't care what kind of torture it is! Please, is there any
way you can help her?

Prison Officer: Hmm, well... if you say so, I might consider
talking to the boss about it...
Really?!

Prison Officer: But an accident happened and we can't hide
it. You'll have to be punished because we need to show the
higher-ups that we're doing our job.
Ugh... that's true...

Prison Officer: However, if you insist that much, I might
just talk to the boss for you. If the boss gives a direct
order, then we might have to lighten the punishment.

Prison Officer: If that happens, even with the strict rules
here, her life might not be taken. Maybe.
Please, I beg you! It would help a lot if you could do that!

Prison Officer: You've got a pretty good body, but I prefer
torturing skinny, gloomy rats. You're not my type. But I
think the boss might like someone like you.

Prison Officer: If it helps me score points with the boss,
then that's fine by me. The rest is up to you whether you
beg or lick ass or whatever. It's none of my business.
So, that means she'll be saved?!

Prison Officer: Hmm? That depends on the boss's mood, so I
can't make any promises.
Prison Officer: Well, whatever, follow me.

Prison Officer: Oi! You lot keep digging in silence!! If you
slack off, I'll kill you!!
